-- Schneider closes sale of sensors business
-- By Natalie Huet
-- Wed Oct 01, 2014 12:01PM EDT
-- None



PARIS, Oct 1 (Reuters) - Schneider electric <SCHN.PA> said on Wednesday it had finalised the sale of its sensors business to private equity firms The Carlyle Group <CGO.O> and PAI Partners.

As part of the deal, Schneider Electric has reinvested some $100 million in the business -- Custom Sensors & Technologies (CST) -- to have a shareholding of about 30 percent.